])\n\n===Former connecting lines===\n* Okusawa station - A 1&nbsp;km 1067mm gauge line, electrified at 600 VDC, from Shin-Okusawa operated between 1928 and 1935, providing a connection to Yukigaya-Otsuka on the [[Tokyu Ikegami Line]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of railway lines in Japan]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Tokyu Meguro Line}}\n{{Tokyo transit}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tokyu Meguro Line}}\n[[Category:Lines of Tokyu Corporation|Meguro Line]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Tokyo]]\n[[Category:1067 mm gauge railways in Japan]]\n[[Category:Railway lines opened in 1923]]\n[[Category:1923 establishments in Japan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox rail line\n| box_width   =\n| name        = Tokyu Meguro Line\n| native_name   = \u6771\u6025\u76ee\u9ed2\u7dda\n| native_name_lang = ja\n| color       = 1E90FF <!-- DodgerBlue -->\n| logo        = {{TQLS|MG|size=25}}\n| logo_width  = \n| image       = Tokyu 3020 Series 3121F 20200125.jpg\n| image_width = 300px\n| caption     = Tokyu 3020 series EMU on the Meguro Line\n| type        = [[Commuter rail]]\n| system      =\n| status      =\n| locale      = [[Tokyo]]\n| start       = {{STN|Meguro}}\n| end         = {{STN|Hiyoshi|Kanagawa}}\n| stations    = 13\n| routes      =\n| daily_ridership   = 388,982 (FY 2018)<ref name=\"TokyuFacts\"/>\n| open        = \n| close       =\n| owner       = [[Tokyu Corporation]]\n| operator    = \n| character   =\n| depot       = \n| stock       = \n| linelength  = {{Convert|11.9|km|mi|abbr=on}}\n| tracklength = \n| tracks     =\n| gauge       = {{track gauge|1067mm|lk=on}}\n| electrification          = 1,500 V DC overhead catenary\n| speed       = \n| elevation   =\n| map         = \n| map_state   = \n}}\n\n{| {{Railway line header|collapse=yes}}\n{{UKrail-header|Route diagram}}\n{{BS-table}}\n{{BS-colspan}}\n*Ex: Express trains stop\n*Lo: only Local trains stop\n----\n{{BS6|||||||&nbsp;}}\n{{BS3|||KHSTa|||{{STN|Urawa-Misono}}|}}\n{{BS3|||STR|||[[Saitama Rapid Railway]]|}}\n{{BS3|||HST|||{{STN|Akabane-Iwabuchi}}|}}\n{{BS3||KHSTa|STR|||{{STN|Nishi-Takashimadaira}}|}}\n{{BS3||STR2|STR3||||}}\n{{BS3||STR+1|STR+4||||}}\n{{BS3||HST|HST|||{{STN|K\u014drakuen}}/{{STN|Kasuga|Tokyo}}|}}\n{{BS3||STRl|ABZg+r|||[[File:Arrow Blue Right 001.jpeg|10px|Right]][[File:Arrow Blue Up 001.jpeg|10px|Up]][[Toei Mita Line]]|}}\n{{BS3|||HST|||{{STN|Shirokane-Takanawa}}|}}\n{{BS3|||LSTR|||[[File:Arrow Blue Up 001.jpeg|10px|Up]][[Tokyo Metro Namboku Line]]|}}\n{{BS5||STRq|tKRZ|STRq|STR+r|||[[File:Arrow Blue Left 001.jpeg|10px|Left]][[Yamanote Line]][[File:Arrow Blue Down 001.jpeg|10px|Down]]|}}\n{{BS5||STRq|tKRZ|STR+r|STR|||[[File:Arrow Blue Left 001.jpeg|10px|Left]][[Sh\u014dnan Shinjuku Line|Sh\u014dnan Shinjuku]], [[Saiky\u014d Line|Saiky\u014d]] lines[[File:Arrow Blue Down 001.jpeg|10px|Down]]|}}\n{{BS5|||tBHF|STR|BHF|0.0|Ex {{STN|Meguro}}||}}\n{{BS5|||tSTR|STR|STRl||||}}\n{{BS5|||tSTRe|STRl|STRq||||}}\n{{BS3|||hKRZWa||||}}\n{{BS3|||hBHF|1.0|Lo {{STN|Fud\u014dmae|Tokyo}}||}}\n{{BS3|||htSTRa||||}}\n{{BS3|||tBHF|1.9|Ex {{STN|Musashi-Koyama}}||}}\n{{BS3|||tBHF|2.6|Lo {{STN|Nishi-Koyama}}||}}\n{{BS3|||tSTRe||||}}\n{{BS3|||tSTRa||||}}\n{{BS3|||tBHF|3.3|Lo {{STN|Senzoku}}||}}\n{{BS3|||tSTRe||||}}\n{{BS3|||TUNNEL2||||}}\n{{BS4||tSTR+l|KRZt|tSTReq|||[[File:Arrow Blue Down 001.jpeg|10px|Down]][[T\u014dky\u016b \u014cimachi Line]][[File:Arrow Blue Right 001.jpeg|10px|Right]]|}}\n{{BS4||tSTR|tSTRa|||||}}\n{{BS4||tXBHF-L|tXBHF-R||4.3|Ex {{STN|\u014cokayama}}||}}\n{{BS4||tSTRe|tSTRe|||||}}\n{{BS4||ABZgl|ABZg+r||||[[File:Arrow Blue Left 001.jpeg|10px|Left]]T\u014dky\u016b \u014cimachi Line[[File:Arrow Blue Up 001.jpeg|10px|Up]]|}}\n{{BS5|HSTq|STRr|STR|||||{{STN|Midorigaoka|Tokyo}}|}}\n{{BS4||STR+l|ABZgr|||Okusawa depot||}}\n{{BS4||KDSTe|BHF||5.5|Lo {{STN|Okusawa}}||}}\n{{BS5|tSTRaq|tSTR+r|tSTRa||||[[File:Arrow Blue Up 001.jpeg|10px|Up]]'''Meguro Line'''||}}\n{{BS4||tXBHF-L|tXBHF-R||6.5|Ex {{STN|Den-en-ch\u014dfu}}||}}\n{{BS4||tABZgl+l|tABZgr+r||||[[File:Arrow Blue Left 001.jpeg|10px|Left]][[T\